  "text": "We can obtain a distributed representation of a word using the Word2Vec software [CITATION_1] which enable us to perform vector addition/subtraction on a word's meaning. The theoretical background is analyzed by [CITATION_2] , where the operation is to factorize a word-context matrix, where the elements in the matrix are some function of the given word and its context pairs. This analysis gives us insight into how the vector is affected by multiple senses or multiple context sets. If a word has two senses, the obtained representation for the word will be a linearly interpolated point between the two points of their senses.",
